[[File:Arnost Muka 1896 Hoeffert.png|thumb|Arnošt Muka (1896)]]

'''Arnošt Muka''' (10 March 1854 – 10 October 1932) was a [[Germany|German]] and [[Sorbs|Sorbian]] writer, linguist and man of science.

Muka was born in Großhänchen which is now in the municipality of [[Burkau]], and studied theology, classical languages and Slavonic in [[Leipzig]]. Because of his activities in connection with the [[Sorbian languages]], he was sent to teach in a [[gymnasium (Germany)|gymnasium]] in [[Chemnitz]] in 1883, and later to [[Freiberg]]. In 1917, he moved back to [[Bautzen]], where he died on 10 October 1932.<ref>{{cite web | title =Weder Preis noch Ehr | work =Der sorbische Gelehrte Ernst Mucke (1854 - 1932) | publisher =National-museum der Sorben | date =2004 | url =http://www.museum.sorben.com/muka/mukadt.htm | accessdate =25 April 2014 | language =German }}</ref>

