{{Infobox academic |name = Douglas Duckworth |image = Douglassduckworth.JPG |image_size = |caption = Douglas Duckworth |birth_date = {{birth date and age|1971|09|04|}} |birth_place = United States |death_date = |death_place = |residence = |citizenship = |nationality = [[United States|American]] |ethnicity = |discipline = [[Buddhist Philosophy]] |work_institutions = [[Temple University]] |alma_mater = [[University of Virginia]] |thesis_title = |doctoral_advisor = |academic_advisors = |doctoral_students = |known_for = |author_abbrev_bot = |influences = |influenced = |prizes = |religion = |footnotes = |signature = }}
'''Douglas S. Duckworth''' (born 1971) is an American academic working in the field of [[Buddhist Philosophy]] and [[Tibetan Buddhism]].
==Career==
Douglas Duckworth currently holds a position at [[Temple University]] in the Department of Religion and has previously taught at Kathmandu University. He is an associate editor of the ''Journal of Buddhist Philosophy'', and has served on steering committees at the [[American Academy of Religion]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cla.temple.edu/religion/faculty/douglas-duckworth/ |title=Dr. Douglas Duckworth |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |website =College of Liberal Arts, Temple University }}</ref>
==Research interests== [[Jamgon Ju Mipham Gyatso|Mipam]] and his school.
